CBRE is delighted to present 9 Somer Avenue, Shepparton for sale. 

Key features:
+ SOMER AVENUE FRONTAGE
+ ACTIVITY CENTRE ZONE (ACZ)
+ LAND: 4,552SQM*

For sale via Expressions of Interest closing: Thursday, 23rd May 2019 at 5pm

*approximate

The portfolio is being offered as two (2) separate opportunities, which can be purchased individually or in an ‘in one line’ basis. The key attributes of both opportunities are summarised as follows:

Property 1 – Value Add Retail Investment Opportunity Leased to Kmart & Coles
• Strategic Victorian retail investment with long term lease to Coles (3,930sqm*) and Kmart (7,070sqm*), expiring July 2020 with no further options
• Efficiently configured retail centre with no specialty tenants
• Estimated annual net income of $1,741,000* excl GST
• Substantial CBD land holding of 21,750 square metres* including 366 ‘at grade’ car spaces*


Property 2 – Retail Development Opportunity – Zoned for a Neighbourhood Shopping Centre (STPA)
• Prime centrally located 16,766sqm*, Business 1 and 5 zoned CBD development site
• Provision for a full line supermarket based shopping centre development (STPA)
• Significant development synergies may be obtained if purchased with Property 1
• Future development may benefit from four (4) active street frontages
• Provision for significant CBD car parking amenity

CBRE Victorian Retail Investments as exclusive sales and marketing agents offer the portfolio by way of a Public Expressions of Interest campaign closing at 3:00pm (AEST) Thursday 12 April 2012.

Acting under instructions from Adam Nikitins and Justin Walsh from Ernst & Young, Receivers and Managers

- Land Area: 11,555sqm*
- Building Area: 4,121sqm*
- Excellent development (STCA) or occupier opportunity
- Large warehouse and processing facility
- Eight (8) titles
- Zoned Commercial 1 (CZ1)
- Vacant possession

Mortgagee Auction: Thursday 27th August 2015 at 11.30am on site.

Under Instructions From PPB Advisory.
(Administrators Appointed) (Receivers & Managers Appointed)

*approx.

A rare opportunity to secure a prime main road retail property with huge upside for growth in one of Victoria's premier regional cities

Significant landholding of 21,696sqm*

Access to over 196* at grade car parks

Holding income from Bunnings until September 2017 to allow for repositioning and re-leasing

Substantial 6,506sqm* existing building to suit various retail uses

Will suit builders, developers and value add investors seeking their next project

*Approx.

+An expansive 2,700sqm* landholding comprising 326 bays over 9 split levels in a freestanding multi deck commercial car park.

+Landlord favoured triple net lease to Care Park, an end-to-end parking service provider, with over 25 years in operation and more than 450 owned and managed car parks across five countries.

+Providing net annual income of $100,000* through a 7 year lease with fixed 2%* annual rental increases.

+A blue-chip retail investment located within the CBD of one of Victoria’s largest regional towns, on the banks of the Goulburn River within the heart of Victoria’s ‘food bowl’, a region which 25%* of the total value of Victoria's agricultural production is sourced.

+One of the largest structures in the immediate catchment, opposite Village Cinemas, Coles, Kmart, Rebel Sport and the area’s main dining and retail precinct.

+Defensive investment asset class, with low operating expenses, increasing demand from commuters and diminishing competition in the car park sector.
